<!-- Why Choose -->
<section class="section why-section" id="why">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="why-grid">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Why Print Forge</span>
        <h2>Engineering-minded.<br><span class="grad-text">Not hobbyist.</span></h2>
        <p style="margin-top:14px;">We approach every job as a fabrication problem to solve — not a print to execute. That means understanding your application, material requirements, and tolerances before we produce anything.</p>
        <div class="why-list">
          <div class="why-item"><div class="why-num">01</div><div><h4>Material-first</h4><p>We specify materials based on your environment — UV exposure, heat, chemical contact, load, or flex.</p></div></div>
          <div class="why-item"><div class="why-num">02</div><div><h4>Practical tolerances</h4><p>Clearances, wall thickness, and layer orientation are chosen for function, not just appearance.</p></div></div>
          <div class="why-item"><div class="why-num">03</div><div><h4>Fast turnaround</h4><p>Most jobs dispatched within 3–5 working days. Rush jobs considered — ask on enquiry.</p></div></div>
          <div class="why-item"><div class="why-num">04</div><div><h4>No minimum orders</h4><p>One prototype or fifty production parts — both handled without tooling surcharges.</p></div></div>
          <div class="why-item"><div class="why-num">05</div><div><h4>File-to-part service</h4><p>Send an STL, DXF, PDF sketch, or photo — we advise from there.</p></div></div>
          <div class="why-item"><div class="why-num">06</div><div><h4>NZ based</h4><p>No offshore delays. Direct contact with the person running your job.</p></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="cap-panel">
          <div class="cap-panel-header">Materials &amp; Capabilities</div>
          <div class="cap-row"><span class="cap-label">FFF Materials</span><span class="cap-val">PLA · PETG · ASA · ABS · Nylon · TPU · CF-filled</span></div>
          <div class="cap-row"><span class="cap-label">Resin (SLA)</span><span class="cap-val">Standard · Engineering · Flexible · Castable</span></div>
          <div class="cap-row"><span class="cap-label">Laser Materials</span><span class="cap-val">Acrylic · Ply · MDF · Cardboard · Leather · Al</span></div>
          <div class="cap-row"><span class="cap-label">Build volume (FFF)</span><span class="cap-val">Up to 300 × 300 × 400 mm</span></div>
          <div class="cap-row"><span class="cap-label">Layer resolution</span><span class="cap-val">0.05 mm (SLA) · 0.1–0.3 mm (FFF)</span></div>
          <div class="cap-row"><span class="cap-label">Finish options</span><span class="cap-val">Raw · Sanded · Primed · Painted · Post-cured</span></div>
          <div class="cap-row"><span class="cap-label">Turnaround</span><span class="cap-val">3–5 working days standard</span></div>
          <div class="cap-row"><span class="cap-label">File formats</span><span class="cap-val">STL · OBJ · STEP · DXF · PDF · Sketch/photo</span></div>
          <div class="cta-mini">
            <p><strong>Not sure what you need?</strong> Send a description, sketch, or photo of the problem you're trying to solve. We'll come back with options and a quote.</p>
            <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="font-size:0.82rem;padding:11px 20px;">Start with a conversation</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

